<div type="translation">
<head>Translation</head>
<p>To the emperor Caesar Traianus Hadrianus Augustus <gap dim="left" extent="unknown" reason="lost" unit="character"/> the gymnasium of the Young Men and the <gap dim="left" extent="unknown" reason="lost" unit="character"/> son of Nikotimos son of Artemidoros son of Zenon <gap dim="left" extent="unknown" reason="lost" unit="character"/> son of Menandros.</p>
</div>
<div type="commentary">
<head>Commentary</head>
<p>There are several other blocks from this series, too effectively erased to be read.</p>
</div>
<div type="history" n="locations">
<head>Locations</head>
<p><rs type="origLocation">?In a gymnasium building</rs>
<rs type="found"><rs type="monuList">Temple/Church</rs>: b reused in the north wall of Temple Church Atrium; e excavated in 1993 at the NW side of the temple; other blocks lying loose.</rs><rs type="lastLocation">on site (1978)</rs>
</p>
</div>
<div type="history" n="text-constituted-from">
<head>Text Constituted From</head>
<p>Transcription (Reynolds).</p>
</div><div type="history" n="record">
<head>History of Recording</head>
